<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/615001053/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Ordinary Call through Progressive Assessment:
A total of 8 practical assignments accounting for 40% of the final grade.
Two midterm exams accounting for 40% of the grade. The minimum grade for both exams is 4/10. In the second exam, the first one can be retaken, including extra questions for such recovery.
A project presented at the end of the course in groups, accounting for 20% of the total grade. Minimum grade required is 4/10.

Ordinary Call through Global Assessment:
A global exam accounting for 60% of the grade. Minimum grade required is 4/10.
An individual final project, accounting for 40% of the total grade. Minimum grade required is 4/10.

Extraordinary Call:
An exam accounting for 60% of the grade. Minimum grade required is 4/10.
An individual project, accounting for 40% of the total grade. Minimum grade required is 4/10.

Clarifications:
The midterm exams are exempting; if passed, those topics will not be asked again (except for content related to them later in the syllabus). In the case of global assessment, the exam will be the same as the final progressive one if the first exempting part was not passed. Regarding the extraordinary call, the exempting parts will no longer be valid, and the entire subject will need to be assessed again.
If a student passes the practical assignments or the exam but fails the subject overall, the passing grade will not be carried over to future years."""@es ;
    ns1:hasEvaluationTrial <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/615001053/2025-26/evaluation/trial1>,
